snippet.textDisplay: Love your  videos!!  I think you need to clarify which direction you install the fuse tap.  If it is installed the wrong way, the new circuit you ran would not be protected by the fuse.  You will need to check for voltage with the fuse tap removed (An empty fuse location).  Establish which socket has voltage.  Then put the red wire leaving the fuse tap on the other socket.  That way voltage will go thru the fuse and then to the new wired circuit.

A terrific design, with only one fundamental flaw. The selling point of this system was to allow the one who "dunnit" the opportunity to remove the offensive odor with stealth. Unfortunately, you chose about the noisiest switch possible. There are a whole host of switches out there that could close this circuit much more quietly. The trick is to balance quietness, reliability and ease of use, so do a little research and you'll have the perfect stealthy stink stifler.
Great design! 😀
